{{Italic title}}
'''''The Encyclopedia Show''''' is a live [[variety show]] and [[reading series]] format founded in [[Chicago]] by Robbie Q. Telfer and Shanny Jean Maney in December 2008 at the [[Chopin Theatre]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chicago.timeout.com/articles/student-guide/87935/student-guide-the-encyclopedia-show |title=Student Guide &#124; The Encyclopedia Show - Time Out Chicago |publisher=Chicago.timeout.com |date=2010-08-01 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref>  Since its founding, it has spread to regular shows in [[Austin]], [[Oklahoma City]], [[Providence, Rhode Island|Providence]], [[Columbus, Ohio]], [[Indianapolis]], [[Somerville, Massachusetts]],<ref>http://bostonpoetryslam.com/encyclopediashow</ref> [[District of Columbia]],<ref>http://www.epediadc.com/</ref> [[Vancouver]] Canada and [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.austinchronicle.com/gyrobase/Issue/story?oid=oid%3A1063422 |title=Everybody's Talking at You: Austin's reading series scene is booking good Austin Books |publisher=AustinChronicle.com |date= |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Solomon |first=Dan |url=http://www.avclub.com/austin/articles/of-bestselling-memoirs-and-penniless-drunks-the-en,43067/ |title=Of best-selling memoirs and penniless drunks: The Encyclopedia Show's vice presidential fact sheet &#124; City Life &#124; The A.V. Club Austin |publisher=Avclub.com |date=2010-07-14 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seoulstyle.com/entertainment.php?aid=0000000326 |title=Seoul Encyclopedia Show |publisher=Seoulstyle.com |date=2010-09-04 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref>

The show follows a research conceit that presents a different topic every month.  Within each topic, artists are assigned subtopics that they have to present new creative material on. The show also juxtaposes real experts in the field regarding the various topics.  Past participants have been [[Bill Ayers]], [[Paul Sereno]], [[Marc Smith (poet)|Marc Smith]], [[Helen Morrison]], [[Roger Bonair-Agard]], and [[Robert Boone]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2010-04-30/entertainment/ct-ott-0430-encyclopedia-show-doit-20100430_1_uic-education-professor-present-original-works-second-city |title=The Encyclopedia Show in Chicago - Chicago Tribune |publisher=Articles.chicagotribune.com |date=2010-04-30 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www3.timeoutny.com/chicago/blog/out-and-about/2009/03/bill-ayers-encyclopedia-show/ |title=Bill Ayers talks explosives at The Encyclopedia Show &#124; The TOC Blog &#124; Time Out Chicago |publisher=.timeoutny.com |date=2009-03-05 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagopublicradio.org/Content.aspx?audioID=36763 |title=Chicago Amplified - The Encyclopedia Show: Dinosaurs |publisher=Chicagopublicradio.org |date=2009-09-02 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagopublicradio.org/Content.aspx?audioID=33169 |title=Chicago Amplified - YCA's LTAB University Presents: The Encyclopedia Show! - The Visual Spectrum |publisher=Chicagopublicradio.org |date=2009-02-04 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagopublicradio.org/Content.aspx?audioID=37604 |title=Chicago Amplified - The Encyclopedia Show Presents! Series 2, Volume 2: Serial Killers |publisher=Chicagopublicradio.org |date=2009-10-07 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagopublicradio.org/Content.aspx?audioID=43047 |title=Chicago Amplified - The Encyclopedia Show Presents! Series 2, Volume 10: The Circus |publisher=Chicagopublicradio.org |date=2010-06-09 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wbez.org/Content.aspx?audioID=41452 |title=Chicago Amplified - The Encyclopedia Show Presents! Series 2, Volume 6: Explorers |publisher=Wbez.org |date=2010-02-03 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref>

In March 2010, the Chicago Encyclopedia Show won the Orgie (short for Original) Theatre Award for 2009's "Best Creation/Curators."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www3.timeoutny.com/chicago/blog/out-and-about/2010/03/2009-orgie-theatre-awards-announced/ |title=2009 Orgie Theatre Awards announced &#124; The TOC Blog &#124; Time Out Chicago |publisher=.timeoutny.com |date=2010-03-07 |accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref>

