{{Infobox film |name = The Legend of Ngong Hills |image = |caption = |director = Kwame Nyong'o |producer = {{plainlist| *Kwame Nyong'o *Wallace Murungi *Alnavaz Amlani }} |screenplay = Alan Barillaro |starring = {{plainlist| *Derek Assetto *Doreen Kemunto *Steve Muturi *Joseph Waruinge }} |music = Jim Pywell |cinematography = |editing = |studio = Apes in Space |distributor = |released = |runtime = 10 minutes |country = Kenya |language = English }} '''''The Legend of Ngong Hills''''' is a 2011 [[Kenya|Kenyan]] animated short film based on a [[Maasai people|Maasai]] folktale. It won the ''Best Animation'' award at the [[8th Africa Movie Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.animationsa.org/news-and-events/kenyas-legend-ngong-hills-wins-amaa | title=Kenyans The Legend on Ngong Hills wins AMAA | publisher=animationsa.org | accessdate=31 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ttfilmfestival.com/2011/07/the-legend-of-ngong-hills/ | title=Trinidad and Tobago Film Festival: The Legend on Ngong Hills | publisher=ttfilmfestival.com | accessdate=31 July 2014}}</ref>
